    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}502{n]}All human passions, all revenge, all pride;{l]
      [l [n}503{n]}I think, speak, act no ill; I do but hide{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}504{n]}Under these words, like embers, every spark{l]
      [l [n}505{n]}Of that which has consumed me—quick and dark{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}506{n]}The grave is yawning … as its roof shall cover{l]
      [l [n}507{n]}My limbs with dust and worms under and over{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}508{n]}So let Oblivion hide this grief … the air{l]
      [l [n}509{n]}Closes upon my accents, as despair{l]
      [l [n}510{n]}Upon my heart—let death upon despair!{q]{l]{lg]{verse-para]

    [verse-para}[lg}[l [n}511{n]}He ceased, and overcome leant back awhile,{l]
      [l [n}512{n]}Then rising, with a melancholy smile{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}513{n]}Went to a sofa, and lay down, and slept{l]
      [l [n}514{n]}A heavy sleep, and in his dreams he wept{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}515{n]}And muttered some familiar name, and we{l]
      [l [n}516{n]}Wept without shame in his society.{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}517{n]}I think I never was impressed so much;{l]
      [l [n}518{n]}The man who were not, must have lacked a touch{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}519{n]}Of human nature … then we lingered not,{l]
      [l [n}520{n]}Although our argument was quite forgot,{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}521{n]}But calling the attendants, went to dine{l]
      [l [n}522{n]}At Maddalo’s; yet neither cheer nor wine{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}523{n]}Could give us spirits, for we talked of him{l]
      [l [n}524{n]}And nothing else, till daylight made stars dim;{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}525{n]}And we agreed his was some dreadful ill{l]
      [l [n}526{n]}Wrought on him boldly, yet unspeakable,{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}527{n]}By a dear friend; some deadly change in love{l]
      [l [n}528{n]}Of one vowed deeply which he dreamed not of;{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}529{n]}For whose sake he, it seemed, had fixed a blot{l]
      [l [n}530{n]}Of falsehood on his mind which flourished not{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}531{n]}But in the light of all-beholding truth;{l]
      [l [n}532{n]}And having stamped this canker on his youth{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}533{n]}She had abandoned him—and how much more{l]
      [l [n}534{n]}Might be his woe, we guessed not—he had store{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}535{n]}Of friends and fortune once, as we could guess{l]
      [l [n}536{n]}From his nice habits and his gentleness;{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}537{n]}These were now lost … it were a grief indeed{l]
      [l [n}538{n]}If he had changed one unsustaining reed{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}539{n]}For all that such a man might else adorn.{l]
      [l [n}540{n]}The colours of his mind seemed yet unworn;{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}541{n]}For the wild language of his grief was high,{l]
      [l [n}542{n]}Such as in measure were called poetry;{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}543{n]}And I remember one remark which then{l]
      [l [n}544{n]}Maddalo made. He said: [q [who}Maddalo{who]}Most
        wretched men{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}545{n]}Are cradled into poetry by wrong,{l]
      [l [n}546{n]}They learn in suffering what they teach in song.{l]{q]{lg]{verse-para]

    [verse-para}[lg}[l [n}547{n]}If I had been an unconnected man,{l]
      [l [n}548{n]}I, from this moment, should have formed some plan{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}549{n]}Never to leave sweet Venice,—for to me{l]
      [l [n}550{n]}It was delight to ride by the lone sea;{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}551{n]}And then, the town is silent—one may write{l]
      [l [n}552{n]}Or read in gondolas by day or night,{l]
      [l [n}553{n]}Having the little brazen lamp alight,{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}554{n]}Unseen, uninterrupted; books are there,{l]
      [l [n}555{n]}Pictures, and casts from all those statues fair{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}556{n]}Which were twin-born with poetry, and all{l]
      [l [n}557{n]}We seek in towns, with little to recall{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}558{n]}Regrets for the green country. I might sit{l]
      [l [n}559{n]}In Maddalo’s great palace, and his wit{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}560{n]}And subtle talk would cheer the winter night{l]
      [l [n}561{n]}And make me know myself, and the firelight{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}562{n]}Would flash upon our faces, till the day{l]
      [l [n}563{n]}Might dawn and make me wonder at my stay:{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}564{n]}But I had friends in London too: the chief{l]
      [l [n}565{n]}Attraction here, was that I sought relief{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}566{n]}From the deep tenderness that maniac wrought{l]
      [l [n}567{n]}Within me—’twas perhaps an idle thought—{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}568{n]}But I imagined that if day by day{l]
      [l [n}569{n]}I watched him, and but seldom went away,{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}570{n]}And studied all the beatings of his heart{l]
      [l [n}571{n]}With zeal, as men study some stubborn art{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}572{n]}For their own good, and could by patience find{l]
      [l [n}573{n]}An entrance to the caverns of his mind,{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}574{n]}I might reclaim him from this dark estate:{l]
      [l [n}575{n]}In friendships I had been most fortunate—{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}576{n]}Yet never saw I one whom I would call{l]
      [l [n}577{n]}More willingly my friend; and this was all{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}578{n]}Accomplished not; such dreams of baseless good{l]
      [l [n}579{n]}Oft come and go in crowds or solitude{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}580{n]}And leave no trace—but what I now designed{l]
      [l [n}581{n]}Made for long years impression on my mind.{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}582{n]}The following morning, urged by my affairs,{l]
      [l [n}583{n]}I left bright Venice.{verse-para]

    [verse-para}After many years{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}584{n]}And many changes I returned; the name{l]
      [l [n}585{n]}Of Venice, and its aspect, was the same;{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}586{n]}But Maddalo was travelling far away{l]
      [l [n}587{n]}Among the mountains of Armenia.{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}588{n]}His dog was dead. His child had now become{l]
      [l [n}589{n]}A woman; such as it has been my doom{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}590{n]}To meet with few,—a wonder of this earth,{l]
      [l [n}591{n]}Where there is little of transcendent worth,{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}592{n]}Like one of Shakespeare’s women: kindly she,{l]
      [l [n}593{n]}And, with a manner beyond courtesy,{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}594{n]}Received her father’s friend; and when I asked{l]
      [l [n}595{n]}Of the lorn maniac, she her memory tasked,{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}596{n]}And told as she had heard the mournful tale:{l]
      [q [who}daughter{who] [indirect]}[l [n}597{n]}That the poor sufferer’s
        health began to fail{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}598{n]}Two years from my departure, but that then{l]
      [l [n}599{n]}The lady who had left him, came again.{l]{q]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [q [who}daughter{who]}[l [n}600{n]}Her mien had been imperious, but she now{l]
      [l [n}601{n]}Looked meek—perhaps remorse had brought her low.{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}602{n]}Her coming made him better, and they stayed{l]
      [l [n}603{n]}Together at my father’s—for I played,{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}604{n]}As I remember, with the lady’s shawl—{l]
      [l [n}605{n]}I might be six years old—but after all{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}606{n]}She left him.{q] … [q [who}Julian{who]}Why, her heart must have been tough:{l]
      [l [n}607{n]}How did it end?{q] [q [who}daughter{who]}And was not this enough?{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}608{n]}They met—they parted.{q]—[q [who}Julian{who]}Child, is there no more?{l]
      [l [n}609{n]}Something within that
        interval which bore{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}610{n]}The stamp of [emph}why{emph] they parted, [emph}how{emph] they met?{q]{l]
      [l [n}611{n]}[q [who}daughter{who]}Yet if thine aged eyes disdain to wet{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}612{n]}Those wrinkled cheeks with youth’s remembered tears,{l]
      [l [n}613{n]}Ask me no more, but let the silent years{l]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}614{n]}Be closed and cered over their memory{l]
      [l [n}615{n]}As yon mute marble where their corpses lie.{l]{q]
    {lg]
    [lg}
      [l [n}616{n]}I urged and questioned still, she told me how{l]
      [l [n}617{n]}All happened—but the cold world shall not know.{l]{lg]{verse-para]
